The Telegraph - Calcutta : Business

 i-flex profit at Rs 45 crore

 Jan. 29 (PTI): Strong revenue growth coupled with improved operating performance helped i-flex Solutions report a rise in net profit at Rs 45.4 crore during the third quarter ended December on a consolidated basis compared with Rs 35.5 crore during the corresponding previous period.

 Total income, on a consolidated basis, for the reporting quarter rose to Rs 300 crore from Rs 208.3 crore during the third quarter of 2003-04. ?The revenue growth coupled with improved operating performance demonstrates that our investments in R amp;D, sales amp; marketing and delivery capability enhancement are yielding success in the global marketplace,? i-flex Solutions chairman and managing director Rajesh Hukku said.

 ?We continue to invest in new initiatives that are aimed at strengthening our leadership position in our marketplace through our unique well-hedged business model,? he added. 

 The product business of the company grew 25 per cent quarter-on-quarter while services business grew 10 per cent.

 The company added 16 new customers in the October-December period to take the total to 528 across 111 countries. It added 13 new customers to its flagship product Flexcube. 




